The paper deals with the intersection of machine learning and economics, specifically exploring the incentives of self-motivated agents in an explore and exploit scheme. This falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The addition of a social network layer also brings in the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and the study of incentives in a society of agents falls under the sub-category of computational social science (cs.SOC). Finally, the use of algorithms to optimize outcomes falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
